<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-10460] ReplicaListValidator format checking is incomplete</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10460</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ConfigHandler.scala#L220&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ConfigHandler.scala#L220&lt;/a&gt;&#160;. The logic is supposed to accept only two cases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;list of k:v pairs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a single &apos;*&apos;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;But in practice, since the disjunction&apos;s second part only checks that the head is &apos;*&apos;, the case where a k:v list is headed by a star is also accepted (and then later broker dies at startup, refusing the value).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This practically happened due to a CruiseControl bug (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/linkedin/cruise-control/issues/1322&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/linkedin/cruise-control/issues/1322&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Observed on 2.4, but seems to be present in HEAD&apos;s source as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
